    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.38-39"/>
                <note type="curatorial">38</note>
                <note type="curatorial">
                    Missouri Collection July 13, 1924
                </note>
                
                <opener>
                    
                    <salute>Dearest Ones:-</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Got a good sleep at Lans will stay all night at Nebraska City &amp; have to <del/>
                drive to Peru tomorrow through mind - 16 miles am well - thinking mostly of you
                there four days from now I will be on this same train bound home. Hurrah! Have sent
                $250 home. Heavy ram last night &amp; all day today, will be in Omaha tomorrow night again - with Judge, then to Wayne. Leave Omaha at 4:30 July 17th and</p> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4b.5.38-39"/>
                <note type="curatorial">39</note>
                <note type="authorial">-2-</note>
                
                <p>will reach home at <unclear/> July 18th. It's been a good trip so far. Only $4 hotel bell this far, must slay in hotel tonight.</p> 
                <p>The railraod is watched out from WI City to Peru. That's why I must trive, It's
                    safe, however, So much love to all of you, Have a lot to tell.</p> 
                <p>This train jumps around like a jackrabbit</p>
                
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        Jno 
                        Daddy. 
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
